From 7641d16b6a4d334516a73e5a8416385ad0427c98 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: WimLee115 <wimlee@>
Date: Mon, 16 Feb 2026 15:22:56 +0100
Subject: Fix monitor mode hard freeze: SKB use-after-free in RX path
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

After recv_frame_monitor() delivered the SKB to the kernel via
rtw_netif_rx(), the PHL RX buffer recycling (phl_release_rxbuf_usb)
zeroed/reused the underlying buffer while the kernel still held a
reference — causing a hard system freeze on packet capture.

Fix: use skb_copy_expand() to create an independent SKB copy with
64 bytes headroom before delivering to the kernel. The original SKB
stays with the recv_frame for normal driver buffer recycling.

Also fix uninitialized adapter pointer in rtw_core_update_recvframe()
error path by moving initialization before potential goto exit, and
add NULL guard at exit label.

